Gratin is a fancy French way of saying this dish is topped with cheesy breadcrumbs and heated under the broiler until brown and crispy. So it essentially translates to "delicious," right? But what takes this dinner to the next level is the fact that it's made in only one pot. Talk about an easy clean-up.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Thinly slice the @Button Mushrooms{8%oz}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @Yellow Onion{1}(halved and peeled). Strip the @Thyme{1/4%oz} leaves of the stems. Discard the stems.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tsp} in a medium #ovenproof pan{} over medium heat. Add the mushrooms, thyme, and onions. Cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened and slightly golden. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1 1/2%cups} to the pan. Bring to a simmer.

> If you don't have an ovenproof pan, transfer to a baking dish before step 5.

Add the @Mushroom Ravioli{9%oz} to the pan. Cover and cook ~{4-5%minutes}. Uncover and cook, spooning the broth over the ravioli, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until ravioli are tender and broth is thickened. If the liquid evaporates before the ravioli are tender, add a splash of water.

> To keep the ravioli from sticking to the bottom, gently shake the pan occasionally.

== Parmesan Breadcrumbs ==

Make the Parmesan breadcrumbs: Meanwhile, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}, a drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper in a #small bowl{}.

== Assembly ==

Carefully fold the @Sour Cream{4%tbsp} into the ravioli. Season with salt and pepper. You should have a thick, creamy sauce. If too thick, add a splash of water.

Sprinkle the pan with the Parmesan breadcrumbs. Place under the broiler for ~{1-2%minutes}, until golden brown. Enjoy!